snippet: The once-derided United Kingdom Independence Party won about a quarter of all votes cast in local elections across England, surprising detractors and calling attention to its policy demands.
abstract: Once-derided United Kingdom Independence Party wins about a quarter of all votes cast in local elections across England, surprising detractors and calling attention to its policy demands; calls for Britain's withdrawal from 27-nation European Union and for stringent immigration controls and rollback of country's welfare system.

byline.contributor: Stephen Castle contributed reporting from London, and Alan Cowell from Paris.

lead_paragraph: The once-derided United Kingdom Independence Party won about a quarter of all votes cast in local elections across England, surprising detractors and calling attention to its policy demands.

headline.seo: UKIP in Britain Gains in Popular Support
headline.main: Insurgent Party in Britain Gains in Popular Support
headline.print_headline: Insurgent Party in Britain Gains in Popular Support
